To create a todo web on desktop, follow these steps: 
1. Open a text editor or an IDE like Visual Studio Code.
2. Create a new HTML file named index.html.
3. Add basic HTML structure, including doctype, html, head, and body tags.
4. Create a div to hold the todo list and a form to add new tasks.
5. Add JavaScript code to handle user input, add tasks to the list, and save data to local storage.
6. Style the todo list using CSS.
Example code:
```
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Todo List</title>
  <style>
    /* add styles here */
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Todo List</h1>
  <ul id="todo-list"></ul>
  <form id="add-task">
    <input type="text" id="task-input" placeholder="Add new task">
    <button type="submit">Add</button>
  </form>
  <script>
    // get todo list and form elements
    const todoList = document.getElementById('todo-list');
    const addTaskForm = document.getElementById('add-task');
    const taskInput = document.getElementById('task-input');
    // add event listener to form submission
    addTaskForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      const task = taskInput.value.trim();
      if (task) {
        // add task to list and save to local storage
        const todoItems = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('todoItems')) || [];
        todoItems.push(task);
        localStorage.setItem('todoItems', JSON.stringify(todoItems));
        todoList.innerHTML += `<li>${task}</li>`;
        taskInput.value = '';
      }
    });
    // load existing tasks from local storage
    const storedTasks = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('todoItems'));
    if (storedTasks) {
      storedTasks.forEach((task) => {
        todoList.innerHTML += `<li>${task}</li>`;
      });
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```
